Someone executed a (additional) diagnostic action on the system. The action (type, target_component, description, outcome) was: 
TYPE: Test,
TARGET: load module input terminals and internal lamp circuit,
DESCRIPTION: With the system powered and connected as normal, measure the DC voltage directly at the two input terminals of the load module (where the control module output cables attach) during a period when the main lamp is ON and again when it is OFF. Then, with the module opened, measure the voltage on the diode’s anode and cathode and across the lamp/indicator pair during both conditions. Determine whether any significant voltage (near 12 V) actually reaches the diode and lamps, and whether the diode is dropping all of it or the lamps are open.,
RESULT: Measured voltage at the load input terminals is about 0.36 V on Load Input Cable (+) and near 0 V on Load Input Cable (−), with no polarity inversion indicated. The diode sees about 0.36 V on its anode and 0.0003 V on its cathode, while both the main lamp and internal indicator lamp each have essentially 0 V across them. No significant voltage (near 12 V) is present at the diode or across either lamp.
